external_knowledge:
- The term "performance summary" refers to a collection of statistics that provide an overview of a team's performance; 
- The average statistics (e.g., average points per game) are calculated by summing up all the points and dividing by the total number of games; 
- The season wins and losses refer to the number of wins and losses within a specific season, which may not be the same as the total wins and losses; 
- Conference wins and losses refer to the number of wins and losses within a specific conference.
